                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/15/2003&nbsp;: 2:33:46 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><font color="blue">Erciyes I like the idea for your Reincarnation spell but the change would have to be non permanent. Plus you then have to deal with issues of races that can not support certain classes. </font id="blue"><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />In defense, I stated that it should follow race/class limitations.  I disagree with the non-permanence. Making the change permanent is the nature of reincarnation and would strengthen the case for clerical resurrection over a druidic reincarnation.  You still have the option of taking it (there is no option to give back that 50 percent rez after you hit "yes" in favour of a higher.  Hey you choose you choose, such is life.  I will meet you halfway and state you could offer a quest via a races cleric guild to restore you to your former self. <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><font color="blue"> like the random race change. But wouldn't it not matter? If you get the random race you don't want, have them cast it again? Would be rather annoying.<br /><br />Let's not forget how annoyed those with EXP penalties would be. 65 levels of ikky or troll or ogre EXP penalty. Everyone would go Gnome or Halfling till 65ish, then change to ikky or troll. Or even Ogre. heh. Doubt that would *EVER* happen.</font id="blue"><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />The coding would be simple..you make it a one shot deal..reincarnation could only be offered per caster once per death.<br /><br />Would it be irritating?  Yes, yes it would for some.  But the original concept was to give druids a form of resurrection, but still keep clerics at the forefront. I say again..it is a matter of choice. Perhaps Im a bit of a cynic, but the moment you make a decision and it turns out poorly..too bad..you had the option, and it was a fair one. Giving druids reincarnation gives them a valuable xp restoring tool with an associated penalty. As per my original post the chance to restore you to your original form was 50 percent, that could be tweaked either way for playability.<br /><br />In any regards would you trade a bit of an xp penalty for future developement at level 65 as compared to losing your equipment deep in the bowels of some dungeon?  Noting that based on statements above you may be able to "quest" to have your true form restored. (ooh there's a title already "Quest for the True Form".)<br /></span></font></td>
