e new dungeons for the loot, and they'll go there if it's good experience.  Just like Sebilis.  There will likely be plenty of people to call on if the need arises.  If there aren't, it's because the loot is lacking, and/or the xp sucks.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">The point is that if a cleric leaves in the middle of a *dungeon*, are you really going to risk it and continue on, all the while knowing that if someone dies it's over for them and you have to CR at zone/beg a cleric from some other zone to come res you? I wouldn't, nor would most other people.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br />And if the group wipes, having a cleric who can rez will do them absolutely no good, and we're back to square one.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">And my point has never been that _druids_ *needed* resses, but that resses should be more available and not be monopolized by one class.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br />Travel has never been easier in this game.  You can get anywhere you need to in a relatively short period of time.  About the only place that's a challenge are the Western Wastes and attached dungeons, which becomes easy if you have someone who can succor you across Siren's Grotto (another ability that's locked up by two classes).<br /><br />Ergo, getting back to the dungeon that contains your corpse shouldn't take long.  If, as some people claim, the new dungeons will have graveyards, then there will be no problem with corpse recovery.  Since we've elimated travel time, and we've eliminated risk of corpse loss, shall we also completely trivialize death itself?  At that rate, why don't we just go play DAoC where you respawn with all your gear, and the rez is gravy?<br /><br />And, as a reminder, resurrection is not an ability that a single class has a monopoly on.  Three classes can rez, including us.<br /></span></font></td>
